    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "### 📚 How It Works\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Scan**: The script iterates through all your GitHub repositories (or a filtered list).\n",
    "2. **Detect**: It looks for `requirements.txt` files and parses the current versions.\n",
    "3. **Compare**: It queries PyPI to check if newer versions of each package exist.\n",
    "4. **Update**: In `update` mode, it creates a new branch, updates the file, and opens a pull request.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 🛠️ Extending to Other Package Managers\n",
    "\n",
    "You can easily extend the `parse_requirements` and `check_outdated_packages` functions to support:\n",
    "- **Node.js (`package.json`)**: Parse `dependencies` and `devDependencies`, check npm registry.\n",
    "- **Java (`pom.xml` or `build.gradle`)**: Parse XML or Gradle files, check Maven Central.\n",
    "- **Go (`go.mod`)**: Parse `require` statements, check proxy.golang.org.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 📅 Scheduling\n",
    "\n",
    "To run this as a weekly health check:\n",
    "1. In Colab, go to **Tools → Command Palette** (Ctrl+Shift+P).\n",
    "2. Search for \"Run on schedule\".\n",
    "3. Set a schedule (e.g., every Monday at 9 AM).\n",
